Digital, lifestyle, and entertainment platform Accelerate has launched Accelerate Plus, a subscription-based video-on-demand platform. The platform, it was disclosed, is set to feature an ensemble of carefully curated high-quality African content available.   Toyin Adekeye’s Bigger Than Africa set for Netflix debut     Fan recounts how scammer failed using Mike Godson’s picture     My plans for Foundation Night, by Ruggedman   At the launch, Accelerate’s Chief Executive Officer, Colette Otusheso, said, “Accelerate Plus is more than a platform for African content for us. It serves as a catalyst for highlighting and promoting an undiluted African narrative in the face of global misconceptions. For this purpose, we have taken deliberate steps to curate authentic and exciting content for Africa by Africans, as well as to create a portal for the rest of the world to access premium African content from anywhere in the world.” She further reaffirmed Accelerate’s ongoing commitment to the development and support of African filmmakers and the creative industry by encouraging African filmmakers and content creators to collaborate with Accelerate to bring this vision to life. Accelerate is the brainchild of Access Bank.